<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If I have a class:</p>

<p>class MyClass{
   //@param InjectClass $injectClass A class instance to be injected
   //@param string $className A string of FQCN
   _constructor(InjectClass $injectClass, $className){
   }
}</p>

<p>I want to use DI to configure this class. Because I want to inject a class name as a string, I need a DI definition. I think this should be enough:</p>

<p>'definition' =&gt; array(
    'class' =&gt; array(
        'MyClass' =&gt; array(
            'methods' =&gt; array(
                '__construct' =&gt; array(
                     'className' =&gt; array('type' =&gt; false ,'required' =&gt; true),
                )
            )
        )
    )
)</p>

<p>However, if use the above definition, the type hinting for $injectClass is ignored, and a string is injected. The issue can be overcome with:</p>

<p>'definition' =&gt; array(
    'class' =&gt; array(
        'MyClass' =&gt; array(
            'methods' =&gt; array(
                '__construct' =&gt; array(
                     'injectClass' =&gt; array('InjectClass' =&gt; false ,'required' =&gt; true),
                     'className' =&gt; array('type' =&gt; false ,'required' =&gt; true),
                )
            )
        )
    )
)</p>

